  "text": "In fact, if Ω is pseudoconvex, then one can find such an H that depends holomorphically on both ζ ∈ Ω and z ∈ Ω ′ ⊂⊂ Ω. In that case H ℓ k has bidegree (k − ℓ, 0). It was proved in [CITATION_1] , see also the proof of Proposition 4.2 in [CITATION_2] , that if U and R are the currents above associated with the Hermitian complex (2.6), then (2.12) f (z)HU + HU f + HR is ∇ ζ−z -closed. Let us fix a non-negative integer ℓ and let g ′ be the component of (2.12) with values in E ℓ , that is,",
